			    STPJS 358</div>
  <div class="topic">The Forgiveness of Sins</div>
  <p class="std">All sins shall be forgiven, except the sin against the Holy Ghost;<span class="footRef">1</span> for Jesus will save all except
  the sons of perdition.<span class="footRef">2</span> What must a man do to commit the unpardonable sin?<span class="footRef">3</span> He must receive the
  Holy Ghost, have the heavens opened unto him,<span class="footRef">4</span> and know God,<span class="footRef">5</span> and then sin against Him. After
  a man has sinned against the Holy Ghost, there is no repentance for him.<span class="footRef">6</span><span class="textFootRef">,a</span> He has got to say that the
  sun does not shine while he sees it; he has got to deny Jesus Christ<span class="footRef">7</span> when the heavens have been
  opened unto him,<span class="footRef">8</span> and to deny the plan of salvation<span class="footRef">9</span> with his eyes open to the truth of it; and from
  that time he begins to be an enemy. This is the case with many apostates of the Church of Jesus
  Christ of Latter-day Saints.<span class="footRef">10</span></p>
  <p class="std">When a man begins to be an enemy to this work, he hunts me, he seeks to kill me, and never
  ceases to thirst for my blood.<span class="footRef">11</span> He gets the spirit of the devil<span class="footRef">12</span>&mdash;the same spirit that they had who
  crucified the Lord of Life&mdash;the same spirit that sins against the Holy Ghost.<span class="footRef">13</span> You cannot save such
  persons;<span class="footRef">14</span> you cannot bring them to repentance; they make open war, like the devil,<span class="footRef">15</span> and awful is
  the consequence.<span class="footRef">16</span></p>
  <p class="std">I advise all of you to be careful what you do, or you may by-and-by find out that you have been
  deceived.<span class="footRef">17</span> Stay yourselves;<span class="footRef">18</span> do not give way;<span class="footRef">19</span> don&rsquo;t make any hasty moves, you may be saved.
  If a spirit of bitterness<span class="footRef">20</span> is in you, don&rsquo;t be in haste.<span class="footRef">21</span> You may say, that man is a sinner.<span class="footRef">22</span> Well, if
  he repents, he shall be forgiven.<span class="footRef">23</span> Be cautious:<span class="footRef">24</span> await. When you find a spirit that wants
  bloodshed<span class="footRef">25</span>&mdash;murder, the same is not of God,<span class="footRef">26</span> but is of the devil.<span class="footRef">27</span> Out of the abundance of the
  heart of man the mouth speaketh.<span class="footRef">28</span></p>
  <div class="topic">&ldquo;In My Father&rsquo;s House&rdquo;</div>
  <p class="std">The best men bring forth the best works.<span class="footRef">29</span> The man who tells you words of life<span class="footRef">30</span> is the man who
  can save you. I warn you against all evil characters who sin against the Holy Ghost;<span class="footRef">31</span></p>
